\subsection{Cover-totality Ext-transport at universe $u+1$ (iter-032)}

Iter-031's source-object iso (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_top_sourceIso}) feeds into the Ext-level transport: the natural iso of source objects induces a $k$-linear isomorphism on the resulting $\Ext$ groups, by pre- and post-composition with $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}$ on the iso's hom and inverse. The classical lemmas $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_comp\_mk\_0}$ ($(\mathtt{mk\_0}\,f).\mathrm{comp}\,(\mathtt{mk\_0}\,g) = \mathtt{mk\_0}\,(f \circ g)$) and $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_id\_comp}$ collapse the round-trip composition through the iso's identity equations $\alpha.\mathtt{hom}\circ\alpha.\mathtt{inv} = \mathtt{id}$ and $\alpha.\mathtt{inv}\circ\alpha.\mathtt{hom} = \mathtt{id}$, witnessing the round-trip.

The result is universe-pinned to $u+1$ (matching the iter-009 $\HModule$ ascription) — \emph{not} to the universe $u$ at which $\HModulePrime$ lives (iter-014). This pinning sidesteps the iter-031 universe mismatch: instead of building a $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ across $\Type\,u \neq \Type\,(u+1)$, we land at $\Ext.\{u+1\}\,(\presheafToSheaf\text{-source}) \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ where both sides are at $\Type\,(u+1)$. The remaining bridge (from $\HModulePrime$ at $\Type\,u$ to $\Ext.\{u+1\}$ at $\Type\,(u+1)$) is iter-033+ work — most plausibly via a small refactor on the iter-014 $\HModulePrime$ declaration to drop its $\Type\,u$ ascription, or via a $\ULift.\{u+1\}$ wrapper, depending on what the cohort survives.

\begin{definition}[Cover-totality Ext-transport at universe $u+1$, iter-032]
  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_top_linearEquiv}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule_top_linearEquiv}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_top_sourceIso, def:Scheme_HModule}
  \leanok
  Let $k$ be a field, $C$ a category with morphism universe $u$, $J : \GrothendieckTopology\,C$, $T : C$ a terminal object (witnessed by $h_T : \mathtt{IsTerminal}\,T$), and assume $\HasWeakSheafify\,J\,(\Type\,u)$, $\HasSheafify\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, and $\HasExt\,(\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k))$. There is a $k$-linear isomorphism
  \[
    \Ext_{u+1}\bigl(
      (\presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,
        ((\yoneda \circ (\Functor.\mathtt{whiskeringRight}\,\_\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathtt{free}\,k)).\mathrm{obj}\,T),\; F,\; n
    \bigr)
    \;\equiv_{\Module k}\;
    \HModule\,k\,F\,n.
  \]
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  Let $\alpha$ denote the iter-031 source-object iso $\HModulePrimeTopSourceIso\,k\,h_T$, with $\alpha.\mathtt{hom} : X_1 \to X_2$ and $\alpha.\mathtt{inv} : X_2 \to X_1$ in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, where $X_1$ is the sheafified-yoneda-source and $X_2 = (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k)$. The desired equivalence $\Ext_{u+1}\,X_1\,F\,n \equiv_{\Module k} \Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n = \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ is built via $\mathtt{LinearEquiv.ofLinear}$ from
  \begin{itemize}
    \item the forward map $(\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}\,\alpha.\mathtt{inv}).\mathtt{precompOfLinear}\,k\,F\,(0+n=n) : \Ext_{u+1}\,X_1\,F\,n \to_{\Module k} \Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n$, and
    \item the inverse map $(\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}\,\alpha.\mathtt{hom}).\mathtt{precompOfLinear}\,k\,F\,(0+n=n) : \Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n \to_{\Module k} \Ext_{u+1}\,X_1\,F\,n$.
  \end{itemize}
  For the round-trip equations, both directions use a four-step rewrite chain: associativity (via $\Ext.\mathtt{comp\_assoc\_of\_second\_deg\_zero}$ in reverse, since the middle factor has degree $0$), composition collapse (via $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_comp\_mk\_0}$ producing $\mathtt{mk\_0}\,(\alpha.\mathtt{hom} \circ \alpha.\mathtt{inv})$ or $\mathtt{mk\_0}\,(\alpha.\mathtt{inv} \circ \alpha.\mathtt{hom})$), the iso identity ($\alpha.\mathtt{inv\_hom\_id}$ or $\alpha.\mathtt{hom\_inv\_id}$ giving $\mathtt{id}$), and identity-elimination ($\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_id\_comp}$). Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-032 pass) confirms the body typechecks and produces kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 (this iteration) materialises the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$, landing at $\Ext_{u+1}\,X_1\,F\,n \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ — sidestepping the iter-031 universe mismatch by pinning to the $\HModule$ universe rather than the $\HModulePrime$ universe. The remaining work — Step 3-finish (the universe-bridge from $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T : \Type\,u$ to $\Ext_{u+1}$, plausibly via small refactor on iter-014 or via $\ULift.\{u+1\}$ wrapper, iter-033+), Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state), and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-033+.

